## Output Format

When you have completed your review, output ONLY valid JSON in one of these formats:

**If the implementation passes all checks:**
```json
{
  "type": "approved",
  "feedback": "optional positive feedback or notes",
  "metadata": {
    "tests_verified": true,
    "build_verified": true,
    "issues_found": []
  }
}
```

**If the implementation needs changes:**
```json
{
  "type": "rejected",
  "feedback": "specific, actionable feedback for the worker explaining what needs to be fixed",
  "metadata": {
    "tests_verified": true,
    "build_verified": true,
    "issues_found": [
      {"severity": "error", "description": "issue description", "file": "path/to/file.rs", "line": 42}
    ]
  }
}
```

The `metadata` field is optional but helps track what was verified. Severity can be: `error`, `warning`, or `info`.

If you reject, provide clear, actionable feedback so the worker knows exactly what to fix.
